The cryptographic primitives in `lib/libzcash-orchard-c/` (Pallas curve,
Sinsemilla hash, RedPallas signatures, ZIP-32 Orchard derivation, ZIP-244
sighash, FF1-AES, F4Jumble, Bech32m, secp256k1 ECDSA, BIP-32, BIP-39, ZIP-244
state machine, HWP wire protocol) are licensed separately under the MIT
License of the `libzcash-orchard-c` repository. See `lib/libzcash-orchard-c/LICENSE`
for the full text and the upstream attribution to trezor-crypto and Gladman AES.

The QR-code generation code in `lib/qrcode/` is by Project Nayuki and is
licensed under its own MIT License (see `lib/qrcode/qrcodegen.c` header).
